 Governor Ambode. Photo: Twitter/AkinwunmiAmbode  “As we all know, Islam is a religion of peace and peace can only be sustained in a just and fair society.”He said apart from the festivities and promotion of social bonding, the celebration was also a way of showing gratitude to God for His love, which made it possible for his administration to experience an atmosphere of peaceful co-existence and religious harmony that contributed significantly to the progress and prosperity so far achieved in the state.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .